criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  diagnosis of IBD for more than 6 months (CD or UC)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  having started new treatment for IBD in the previous 6 months (in the case of anti-TNF
             and immunosuppressive therapy) or 2 months (in the case of steroid or aminosalicylate
             therapy)

          -  cognitive impairment;

          -  currently undergoing any form of psychological intervention;

          -  current diagnosis of severe psychiatric illness (severe depression, psychotic illness,
             bipolar disorder, substance abuse) or suicidal ideation;

          -  diagnosis of other serious health condition;

          -  pregnancy.
